The paper deals with texture synthesis and style transfer using convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) research. The paper also discusses the use of localized style losses, which is a technique used in multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper proposes improvements to existing methods, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories.
